# Data Management

## Shared state

- Hold app state in Poise `Data` (settings, caches, pools)
- Share with `Arc`; mutate behind `tokio::sync::RwLock` when needed
- Expose small async helpers on `Data` instead of leaking lock details

## Caching

- Prefer bounded caches with TTL (e.g. moka) for hot Discord/user lookups
- Invalidate or TTL-expire after writes that change cached values

## Database

- Use pooled connections (`sqlx` pool options with a modest `max_connections`)
- Prefer prepared / typed queries; map DB errors into bot error types
- Batch inserts/updates when writing many rows

## Concurrency

- Don't hold write locks across Discord API awaits
- Read lock for lookups; upgrade/write only for mutations
